cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.NI 

The paper discusses a methodology for monitoring processes running on hosts in a corporate network using machine learning algorithms. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as the focus is on identifying malicious activity. The use of machine learning algorithms also suggests a potential fit for the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). The methodology also involves distributed collection and processing of data, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
